    <div class="secondarytitle">
      <h2>Hawaiian Design pt. 1</h2>
        <span class="stacked">
            <p>In Kona, Hawaii to design <a href="comfearms.html">Comfe Arms</a>, our newest product. Kona is home to the IRONMAN Triathlon and it seemed like the perfect place to begin designing a new sports band for people who get outdoors and carry their smart phones / music players. Here are a few things the team has learned about designing a product here.</p>
            <img class="righted" src="<%= asset_path 'triathlon_trail.png' %>" width="350" height="248" style="padding: 15px;" alt="triathlon trail view" />
            <p>Besides the warm weather, Kona offers direct access to actual customers on the trail. The best designs seem to always emerge in the places where products are intended for use. Since Comfe Arms is meant for runners, bikers, and walkers of all skill levels, we decided to get out on the trail and find out what it's actually like.</p> 
            <p>The IRONMAN is tough. 112 miles of cycling and another 26.2 miles of running (plus a 2.4 mile swim). The trail is a strong cocktail of heat and wind and sun. Rolling hills mix with sky-filled lava fields. Some of the best runners and bikers live and train here.</p>
            <p>Living and working in the community has given us a chance to understand the challenges athletes face. The first checkpoint was to find out what other products existed and if they made us (and others) unhappy. So many problems surfaced: Plasticy cases. Bands that buckle down as tight as  tourniquets. Moisture leaking through to the phone. Bands that don't stay in place. Etc. etc.</p>
            <p>Understanding the problems with existing products has been a boon to the work. Everything that follows--all the capital, all the tech, and all the brainpower--goes to solve the problems. Maybe that's true for all endeavors. Defining a clear problem is critical for success. Problems establish a finish line to aim for and help us picture solutions in our heads. The problems discovered here have also given key insights that have helped Comfe Arms become radically different and better than competing products.</p>
            <p class="righted">11/27/12</p>
        </span>
    </div>
